    "chemicalDescription": [
      "s-Octopus Pentapeptide-1 SP is a single chain peptide consisting of arginine, isoleucine, leucine and proline. It is synthetically produced based on a sequence from S1 Type peptidase found in the octopus Hapalochlaena maculosa. The parent protein contains a maximum of 182 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
